# Set up 3D Secure (3DS)

How to set up 3DS payment authentication depends on:

- which Payment Service Provider (PSP) you're using
- if you want to set up 3D Secure 2 (3DS2), which adds an extra layer of identity confirmation before your user pays

You can [read more about 3DS2](xxx).

## Stripe

You do not need to do anything, because we set up 3DS2 on your service by default.

## ePDQ

1. Sign in to your [ePDQ account](https://payments.epdq.co.uk/Ncol/Prod/BackOffice/login/index).
2. Go to __Configuration__ then  __Payment methods__.
3. Select __3D Secure__.
4. Check that 3DS is on.
5. Select the account you want to set up on the [__My services__](https://selfservice.payments.service.gov.uk/my-services) page in the GOV.UK Pay admin tool.
6. In the settings, select the __View__ link under __3D Secure__.
7. Select __On__.

## SmartPay

1. Select the account you want to set up on the [__My services__](https://selfservice.payments.service.gov.uk/my-services) page in the GOV.UK Pay admin tool.
2. In the settings, select the __View__ link under __3D Secure__.
3. Select __On__.

You do not need to do anything in your Smartpay account.

## Worldpay

### Set up 3DS

1. Ask your Worldpay account manager to set up 3DS on your merchant code for all payments.
2. Once Worldpay have set up your merchant code, select the account you want to set up on the [__My services__](https://selfservice.payments.service.gov.uk/my-services) page in the GOV.UK Pay admin tool.
3. In the settings, select the __View__ link under __3D Secure__.
4. Select __On__.

### Set up 3DS2 (3DS Flex)

You'll need to pay a fee to Worldpay to use 3DS Flex.

You need your 3DS Flex details to set up your account. Ask your Worldpay account manager if you do not have them.

1. Select the account you want to set up on the [__My services__](https://selfservice.payments.service.gov.uk/my-services) page in the GOV.UK Pay admin tool.
2. In the settings, select the __View__ link under __3D Secure__.
3. Select __On__.
4. Copy your 3DS Flex details into the [PSP settings in your GOV.UK Pay account](https://selfservice.payments.service.gov.uk/your-psp).
5. Check your account still works by [making a payment with a real payment card](/switching_to_live/#6-check-your-live-account-works).
